(845, 1, '2016-01-13 09:13:35', '2016-01-13 17:13:35', 'This policy describes how we treat the personal information we collect. This includes when you use the www.majorcraft-america.com website, the Major Craft mobile app, or contact our customer service department. It also includes when you visit us on any social media pages, like Twitter, Facebook or Instagram. By interacting with us, you consent to these practices.\r\nWE COLLECT INFORMATION FROM AND ABOUT YOU.\r\nWe collect contact information, including profile information and contact information. We collect payment information, like your credit card number when you purchase a product on the www.majorcraft-america.com website. We collect the information you post in a public space, like our social media pages. \r\nWe offer you the choice to utilize the www.majorcraft-america.com website or app. If you create a profile on or otherwise use the www.majorcraft-america.com website or app, you are specifically consenting to the use of any personal information you have provided to us as set forth herein and in the Terms of Use.\r\nIf you use the www.majorcraft-america.com website or app, we may collect information about your browser, the type of device, computer and technical information about your means of connection to the app or website, such as operating system, Internet service providers utilized or other similar information. We may look at what site you came from, or what site you visit when you leave us. We collect this information using the tracking tools, like browser cookies. \r\nWE COLLECT INFORMATION IN DIFFERENT WAYS.\r\nWe collect information directly from you. For example, if you create a profile on the www.majorcraft-america.com website or app, we collect your information. We also collect information if you contact our customer service department. \r\nWe collect information from you passively. For example, we use tracking tools like browser cookies.\r\nWe get information about you from third parties. For example, our business partners may give us information about you. Social media platforms may also provide information about you. \r\nWE USE INFORMATION AS WE DESCRIBE.\r\nWe use information to improve our understanding of your interests and concerns. We may get your information to make www.majorcraft-america.com better. We may use your information to customize your experience and to tailor our marketing activities to fit your needs and interests. We may combine information we get from you with information about you that we receive from third parties.\r\nWe use information to respond to your requests or questions. We may use your information to answer your questions or provide information you request.\r\nWe use information for security purposes. We may use information to protect our company, our customers, our employees, and the www.majorcraft-america.com website and app. We also use information to collect and enforce accounts and to prevent fraud. \r\nWe use information for marketing purposes. There may be third party offers or products that you may find interesting. We may call you, or send you emails or text messages. We may use other means as they arise. We may also use push notifications on our mobile app. \r\nWe use information to communicate with you about your account or our relationship. We may contact you about changes to the www.majorcraft-america.com website and app, or regarding service updates. We may also contact you about feedback or about this privacy policy or our terms of use.\r\nAdditionally, we use information to maintain transaction and other business records. We will do so for as long as necessary. We also use information for internal purposes. This includes administrative and audit purposes. We also use information to meet legal, insurance and processing requirements. We will also use information as otherwise allowed by law, including if we have notified you. We will seek your permission if we are legally required to do so.\r\n\r\nWE MAY SHARE INFORMATION WITH THIRD PARTIES.\r\nWe will share information with third parties who perform services on our behalf. For example, we share information with vendors who send emails for us. We may also share personal information with service providers that help us operate the www.majorcraft-america.com website and app, or run promotions.\r\nWe may share your information with our parent and affiliated companies for various reasons including internal audits, management, billing or administrative purposes. This includes future subsidiaries or affiliates.\r\nWe may share information with our business partners. For example, we will share information with third parties who jointly sponsor an event or promotions with us.\r\nIf we merge with another company, or part or all of our business or assets are transferred, assigned or sold to another company, we may share your information with that company. Your personal information will be disclosed to our successor or assign in these circumstances that can use and disclose your information for substantially the same purposes as set out in this privacy policy.\r\nWe will disclose your information if we think we must to comply with the law or to protect ourselves. This includes compliance with laws outside of the United States that may apply to us. We may share the information if a government agency or investigative body requests. We may share information when we are investigating potential fraud. This may include fraud during a sweepstakes or promotion.\r\nYOU HAVE CERTAIN CHOICES ABOUT SHARING AND MARKETING PRACTICES.\r\nYou may contact us to have your information updated or deleted from our database. Please send us an email at info@majorcraft-america.com. We will make reasonable efforts to service your request in a timely manner.  \r\nTo stop receiving any marketing messages (including emails), follow the instructions in any promotional message you get from us or send us an email at info@majorcraft-america.com. Opt-out requests will be processed without delay, but may not take effect immediately. Even if you opt out of getting marketing messages, we will still send you transactional messages. These include responses to your questions or information about your account. We may still use your information for internal purposes, like maintaining our website. \r\nIf you don’t want us to share your information with third parties for their promotional purposes, please contact us at info@majorcraft-america.com\r\nTo learn how to manage cookies and other tracking tools, please go to the “Tracking” section at the end of this privacy policy.\r\nYou can control tools on your mobile device. Among other things, you can turn off the GPS locator or push notification on your mobile device. Each push notification has an “unsubscribe” link.\r\nMAJORCRAFT-AMERICA.COM AND OUR APP ARE MEANT FOR ADULTS.\r\nWe do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children without permission from a parent or guardian. If you are a parent or legal guardian and think your child has provided us with information, please send us an email at info@majorcraft-america.com.\r\nWE USE STANDARD SECURITY MEASURES.\r\nWe use standard physical, electronic and procedural security measures to protect personal information in our control against loss or theft. We also use these measures to protect against unauthorized access.\r\nWhile we use standard security measures, the Internet is not 100 percent secure. We cannot guarantee that any of your personal information stored or sent to us will be completely safe. We encourage you to use caution when using the Internet.\r\nWE MAY LINK TO THIRD PARTY SITES OR SERVICES THAT WE DO NOT CONTROL.\r\nYou may be able to access certain third party sites from www.majorcraft-america.com or the app. This includes social media sites. This privacy policy does not apply to those third party sites. We advise you to check the privacy policies of all third party sites you visit to find out how they handle your personal information. We are not responsible for those third party websites.\r\n\r\n\r\nWE STORE INFORMATION IN AND OUTSIDE OF THE UNITED STATES.\r\nInformation that we or our vendors maintain may be stored, processed or accessed both within and outside of the United States. You understand and agree that we may transfer your information to the United States or elsewhere and that the laws of these countries may not afford the same level of protection as those in our country. www.majorcraft-america.com is subject to United States law.\r\nWE MAY UPDATE THIS PRIVACY POLICY.\r\nWe will notify you of any material changes as required by law. We will post an updated copy of our website. Please check this page for updates.\r\nTRACKING\r\nYou can control tracking tools. Most Internet browsers give you the ability to control cookies. How you control cookies depends on the type of cookies. Some browsers can be set to reject browser cookies. If you block cookies on your browser, certain features on www.majorcraft-america.com may not work.\r\nPLEASE CONTACT US IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS.\r\nIf you have any questions, you may write us an email us at info@majorcraft-america.com. \r\n', 'Terms and Conditions', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '419-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 09:13:35', '2016-01-13 17:13:35', '', 419, 'http://majorcraft.vmsrv16.inside.cactussoft.biz/2016/01/13/419-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
